>>
>>As another example, let us look at Lord
>  Vaamana. His story is a perfect demonstration of how wisdom/discrimination
> operates.
>>
>>He was born as a learned pygmy. He filled the entire cosmos to rid earth of
>> a charitable demon king with many great qualities.
>>
>>Wisdom/discrimination makes one humble and unassuming. When one is doing
>> good work but tainted with demonic qualities (e.g. pride or attachment),
>> one's discrimination is not pleased until that pride is suppressed. When
>> wisdom fills one's entire consciousness, then demonic qualities are
>> completely suppressed.
>>
